<br>
Correct. Mythic tried there best to ‘split the difference’, if you will. Each realm has ample space where a player who never wants to PvP can level up in peace, without fear of random gankage(at least from other players, roaming-purple-mobs suck ass). The Frontier is a supplement to that space, where players who want to experience the Realm vs. Realm aspect of the game can go to explore, exp and fight with other people.<br>
<br>
<font color=fff00>how does this affect a city seige?<br>
If so,then can you walk into another realm and slay lower levels?<br>
If not then how do you protect your city?</font><br>
<br>
Grouping these three for ease. I can answer all three at the same time.<br>
<br>
There’s no newbie-slaying in this game, unless said newbie walks into the Frontier zone and wanders away from the safety of his [very] Uber realm guards who stand at the gate. That being said, there is no city sieges. I really don’t think its possible to get past the guards at the realm gates. At level 37 they would nuke/bow me from twice player spell range for about 400-500 points of damage a hit. No need to protect your city.<br>
<br>
Forts, on the other hand, require protection and they lie in the Frontier zones. They contain relics and are one of the prime draws of RvR combat. If you manage to steal the relic from an enemy fort, it grants everyone in your realm a bonus as long as you have it(1 has a bonus to melee, other a bonus to spells. More to be added later). You only get this bonus if you have both of your relics and acquire a third or forth so you need defense as well as offense.<br>
<br>
<font color=fff00>Can you attack other realms if they are near your city or neighboring zones?</font><br>
<br>
